    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Diesel Engine Diagnostic Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Diagnostic Software
        Operation - Reset Change Engine Oil Interval Message - Using Cruise Switches
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Using Cruise Switches</title>
        <figure id="f27003057" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D3172.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Switches for CRUISE ON and RESUME/ACCEL</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Reset the change engine oil message feature as follows:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the parking brake (required for correct ESC signal).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn ignition switch to ON.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The entire sequence must be completed within twelve seconds. The change engine oil message will
                    now turn off and will activate when the next oil change is due.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and release both the CRUISE ON and RESUME/ACCEL switches four times within 6
                seconds.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press and hold both the CRUISE ON and RESUME/ACCEL switches for 3 seconds.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release both Cruise buttons.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
